OL,3,CAlderney 'living beyond its means'
OL,4,Cwarns senior politician
OL,6,F"The cost of transferred services such
OL,7,Fas healthcare, education, the airport
OL,8,Fand emergency services exceed the
OL,9,Ftaxes paid to the Bailiwick to help to
OL,10,Fpay for these.
OL,12,F"We entered a fiscal union (with
OL,13,FGuernsey) which initially resulted in
OL,14,Fus producing a surplus of revenue
OL,15,Fversus the cost of transferred
OL,16,Fservices.
OL,18,F"This is not the case today... this is
OL,19,Fnot a sustainable position."
